# Single source of truth

Each fact, rule, or convention lives in **one** canonical artifact. Everywhere else **points**—never copies.

## Artifact roles

| Role | Examples | May contain |
|------|----------|-------------|
| **Define** | Skills, rules | Full rule text |
| **Enforce** | `biome.jsonc`, `scripts/check-architecture.ts` | Machine-checkable constraints |
| **Index** | `docs/enforcement-inventory.md` | Labels, owners, links only |
| **Link** | README, PR bodies, diagnostics | Pointers to the canonical source |

## When writing or editing

- **New standard** → define it in the matching skill or config; add one row to the inventory if it is a project standard.
- **Existing standard** → edit the canonical artifact only; update pointers if the location changed.
- **Comments and error messages** → name the canonical source (e.g. `project-structure` skill, `biome.jsonc`), not a summary of the rule.
- **Do not** restate skills, lint config, or workflow rules in other rules, docs, README, or script headers.

## Inventory

`docs/enforcement-inventory.md` maps standards to enforcement owners. Keep it an index—definitions stay in the linked artifact.
